    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get that the veto power is a problem, but saying it's a 'cop-out' seems pretty strong. isn't the whole point of the UN to provide a forum where these powers can negotiate so we don't end up in a world war? like, even if it's imperfect, isn't there a huge benefit to having at least some kind of international legal framework in place?",
